ick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Alice Wylley was born in 1381, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Richard Wylley."},"et":{"1381–":"1381–Surnud","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1381–Female":"1381–Surnud","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","liv 1575":"1575","1470":"1470","1381":"1381","Prior Marson, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Calverley,Yorkshire,England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thorley, Bishops Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1381–":"1381–Kuollut","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1381–Female":"1381–Kuollut","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","liv 1575":"1575","1470":"1470","1381":"1381","Prior Marson, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Calverley,Yorkshire,England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thorley, Bishops Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1381–":"1381–Décédée","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1381–Female":"1381–Décédée","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","liv 1575":"1575","1470":"147